<font color="#FF0000">MY FAREWELL</font><br>
<tt>Fri Feb 20 13:27:25 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
In the period that this site has been on-line, I have started as a Vietnam Veteran who was recently fired from a long-term job, who was hurting from that experience but I knew that I had nothing to be ashamed of.  <br><br>
I have met some remarkable people at this site, and it is appropriate that Doc Del make the first entry of what may be the last string on this site.  Doc Del and many others have inspired me, helped me work through many of my feelings from Vietnam onward, and helped make this an inspiring site.  <br><br>
For those who tuned in lately, we began this to help others understand that there were many stories which had not been told.  Since, there are literally hundreds of different experiences written up here that would otherwise have been lost to this world.  Marc Weiss and the others who conceived of and maintained this site can be proud of their accomplishment--this is unparalleled in our nation's experience, and should provide a lot of material for many purposes over the next century.  <br><br>
To Ed , Arthur, Cookie, Doc Del, Mike Toliver, ClassLass, and the others who helped me through this period, I want to tell you that I have finally landed a good job.  It has taken over 100 applications, but it has happened.  One writer recently indicated that there is some discrimination concerning Vietnam Veterans in the job field, and that may be true, I don't know.  I do know that my new employer has full knowledge of my service background, and they had asked for it on their application.  <br><br>
Ed, a special note of thanks to you.  I appreciated and used that story of the White Wolf and the Black Wolf at a time when my wife was really down--it helped me tremendously.  I would encourage all to read Ed's writings on the thread titled &quot;Inner Circle.&quot;  <br><br>
If any are interested, we had a very in-depth internet discussion, some of which is in the &quot;Forum&quot; section of this site.  I have the full document of this discussion, which is several hundred pages long.  Marc also has a similar document.<br><br>
Marc, I have only one further suggestion, and that is that an index be made of topics (not right away, but it could be someone's project sometime) so that people could better access the writings of Ed, Doc Del, and others here.  <br><br>
This has been a site of healing.  For this, I thank everyone involved.  It has helped me through a very troubling period in my life.<br><br>
This is probably my last posting, as I will be out-of-town this weekend.  I wish all, including Doc Spatz, well for future.
